<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/521</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-20T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6649. Referring your 8670, February 14, 11 p.m. Cannot see how
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>
                                can be burdened with detail involved in statistical subcommittee of
                                Blockade Council, as your cable seems to indicate. Will send
                                statistician to London to represent us on that body if you so
                                desire.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>